Another parent said Mr Rawlings’ photo went to everyone in her son’s Year 9 class, adding: ‘I also noticed it was sent at 2.39pm on Tuesday – during school time.

‘What on earth was he thinking? I know he was probably trying to connect with the kids but it’s a silly way to do it.’

She claimed the teacher was quite happy to add pupils on his Facebook account.

